# Shared test configuration template.
# Copy this file to .env.test for local secrets and machine-specific values.

# Patrol / emulator identity
PATROL_GOOGLE_TEST_EMAIL=test-account@example.com

# General integration-test identities
TEST_USER_EMAIL=user-test@example.com
TEST_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin-test@example.com

# Add local-only secrets in .env.test, for example:
# TEST_USER_PASSWORD=
# TEST_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
# PATROL_GOOGLE_TEST_PASSWORD=

# FCM Admin Service Configuration (SECURITY SENSITIVE)
# IMPORTANT: NEVER commit actual private keys to version control!
# 
# For development/testing, set FCM_PRIVATE_KEY as a compile-time environment variable:
#   flutter run --dart-define=FCM_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"
#
# For production, use one of these secure alternatives:
#   1. Firebase Admin SDK with service account JSON file
#   2. Google Cloud Secret Manager
#   3. Environment-specific configuration management system
#
# To generate a service account key:
#   1. Go to Firebase Console > Project Settings > Service Accounts
#   2. Click "Generate New Private Key"
#   3. Store the key securely (never commit to git)
#   4. Add .env.test and actual .pem/.json key files to .gitignore